commitResults.messageTitle: Update file name and edited isEmpty() condition check
commitResults.messageBody:
File name was previously Duke, unchanged from the original despite the change in the name since the first commit. There was also a condition check that could have been shortened.

File name has been appropriately changed and the condition has been updated.

commitResults.messageTitle: Create new class to handle data
commitResults.messageBody:
The chatbot previously did not have a way to handle storing data after closing.

To prepare for the implementationn of data storage, a text file has been created alongside a directory and a new class, DataHandler is created to translate this file into
respective Tasks.

The saving function was previously only implemented partiallly. There were also some display bugs where the separator line was not printed where it should have been.

Completed the saving function and fixed the bugs.

Events and deadlines did not properly use dates and times in their implementation previously, allowing for unmeaningful dates and times.

LocalDateTime has been implemented and some small String irregularities have been fixed

commitResults.messageTitle: Add new classes for extra OOP
commitResults.messageBody:
Previous implementation had too many steps crammed into the main method, leading to messy code.

Added Command classes and subclasses to categorize the commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Ui class and fix errors in command classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Ui displays are still executed in main class and could be furthur separated with oop

Created the UI class to store all UI messages.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update main method in Puke class
commitResults.messageBody:
After all the classes were changed in the previous commit, the main class no longer ran properly.

Changed the main class too run properly with the new coode

Update Puke.java to fit coding standard

commitResults.messageTitle: Correct grammar errors in Javadoc comments
commitResults.messageBody:
Certain grammatically incorrect words were being used previously in the Javadoc comments

Changed these words to be grammatically correct

Previously, it was difficult to check through the full length of code for code standard violations

Checkstyle is implemented to automatically detect these violations

commitResults.messageTitle: Create and sort each class into its proper package
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, all classes were in the same file and thus in the same package, leading to messier coding.

Created new folders and packages and sorted each class into its appropriate package.

Previously, there were still many files not in a sub package, leading to messy file organization

Created a new package "managers" in order to store classes that handle data. Also created a dummy method in preparation for GUI creation.

Previously, there was no GUI functionality

Added in a barebones GUI to be improved in the next commit

Previously the GUI implementation was barebones and the UI class was handling messages displayed in the text based UI.

Changed the command classes to generate the messages required by the UI, rendering the UI class obselete. UI class has been deleted and a more functional GUI was implemented that managed to output the messages previously used by Puke.

The startup message had been removed previously while implementing the GUI

Startup message has been re-added

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assert statements to document assumptions
commitResults.messageBody:
There are no assert statements which causes some incorrect inputs
to not trigger an exception. There is also an unused UI class
that was previously used to output responses.

Assert statements are added to document assumptions and prevent
more incorrect inputs which cause exceptions. The unused UI class
was also deleted.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add more assert statements to document more assumptions
commitResults.messageBody:
Some classes had assumptions but did not have assert statements to
document them.

More assert statements are added in these classes to document the
assumptions.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactored segments of code to improve code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
There were many message strings that could have been static
variables.

Changed these Strings to static variables in their respective
classes.
A-CodeQuality
Branch-A-assertions

There is a segment of code that was previously used to run the
program before the GUI was implemented.

Removed this segment of code to improve readability.

There was no tagging function for the tasks.

Added tagging function.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change variable names to fit coding style
commitResults.messageBody:
Variable names for some Booleans did not follow coding style.

Changed these names to better describe their function.

Some of these Booleans were also left unused after changing the UI
to a GUI. This should be addressed when the GUI is improved.

The GUI was previously not very pleasant to look at and did not have
any indicators when an error occurred.

Added extra dialog box formatting to change colour depending on
whether an error occurs and ensured that the full textbox appears
when longer messages are sent.

Many JUnit tests implemented previously were rendered obsolete due
to some classes being deleted,

Added more JUnit tests to make up for it.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add bot name in GUI window
commitResults.messageBody:
GUI window was previously empty.

Added the name of the bot in the window and added a screenshot of
the bot in preparation for creation of a User Guide.

User Guide file was not properly set up.

Edited the User Guide file in preparation for finalizing the bot.

User guide previously had unnecessary components which diminished
the formatting.

Removed certain sections to improve formatting.

The exit command previously did not work after implementing the GUI.

Fixed the command and allowed it to close the program when executed.
Also removed the launcher class and changed the GUI to launch from
the puke class instead.
